 Java Development Projects

A collection of Core Java and Advanced Java projects created to strengthen programming, object-oriented design, and software development skills.

 Topics Covered
- Core Java
- OOPs
- Collections Framework
- Exception Handling
- File Handling
- Multithreading
- JDBC
- Java 8 Features


 Projects Included

 Level 1 (Basic)

1. CBSE Percentage Calculator
  Calculates the percentage based on marks entered by the user.

2. Sum Three Numbers
 Calculates the sum of three numbers entered by the user.

3. CGPA Calculator
 Computes the CGPA using the marks or grades provided by the user.

4. Greeting User
 Generates a personalized greeting message using the user's name.

5. Kilometer to Meter Converter
 Converts distance from kilometers to meters.

6. Integer Checker
 Checks whether the user-entered value is an integer.

7. String to Lowercase Converter
  Converts all characters of a string to lowercase.

8. Replace Spaces with Underscores
  Replaces all spaces in a string with underscores.

9. Letter Template Generator
  Replaces placeholders in a letter template with user-provided values.

10. Detect Multiple Spaces
  Detects double and triple spaces in a given string.

11. Escape Sequence Formatter
  Formats text using Java escape sequence characters such as `\n` and `\t`.

12. FormattedLetterGenerator
  Formats a user-entered message using Java escape sequence characters for better readability.

13. Leap Year Checker
  Checks whether a given year is a leap year using conditional statements.

14. Website Type Checker
  Identifies the type of website based on its domain extension.

15. Pattern Printing
    Prints different star patterns using nested loops in Java.

16. Sum of First N Even Numbers
    Calculates the sum of the first N even numbers using a loop.

17. Multiplication Table
    Generates the multiplication table of a given number in normal and reverse order.

18. Factorial Calculator
    Calculates the factorial of a number using for and while loops.


Level 2 (Intermediate)

1. Rock-Paper-Scissors 
   A simple console-based Rock Paper Scissors game built using Java.



